    * getting started
    * creating tasks
    * organizing tasks
    * doing tasks
    * import / export
    * learn from momentum app -- focus on beauty, simplicity, wisdom (e.g. quote)
  * try to get one or more quotes from people who like it (eventually)
  * privacy policy


Main Page 
  * link to a FAQ page
  * link to a support page
  * other than that, a SPA from now on

  0. Choose a Stack or List
    
  1. Click a button to get a task or make a new one:
    a. new task
    b. hit me! (a task is selected for you, see gory details about how that works below)
    c. choose task (you pick which task)
  2. Once you've got a task, you do one of these:
    a. discard it - back to main (to get or create a new task)
    b. edit it
    c. split it (make it into two or more separate tasks)
    d. expand it (add one or more child tasks)
    e. link it (edit what it depends on, or what depends on it)
    f. do it
    g. promote it to a whole separate Stack or List
    h. delete it
  3. One you're doing a task, you can:
    a. go back to the previous stage
    b. start a timer
    c. track your progress
    d. edit it
    e. finish it
    f. stop working on it
    g. delete it

For a Stack, you can:
  1. Reorder tasks at the top level (e.g. those with the same depth)
  2. Add or edit notes attached to any task
  3. Add or edit notes attached to the whole stack

For a List, you can:
  1. Add or edit notes attached to any task
  2. Set a deadline, priority, or importance for a task
  3. Make a task into a subtask of another
  4. Make a subtask into a separate task

